Connecting to Wifi Netow0rk

To verify if youre connected 

run ipconfig or go to wifi properties
	--> should have a legitimate ip address 
		example 192.168.X.X
		
NOTE: If you type in a wrong password, It will not tell you that the password that
	you have type in is wrong.It will not just gonna let you connect and as a result 
	you will get a apipa(automatic private ip addressing) 169.254.X.X
	
	
WPS --> Wifi Protected Setup
	
Notes : >> from windows, you can easily view all nearby wireless network
		>> make sure you know the ssid and password for the network that you want to connect to
		>> using wps to connect to a wifi network with a single button sounds great-- but dont use it